body_html:
Good news is it builds. Bad news is when I try checking if it works with,

python3 -c 'from caffe2.python import core'

that fails. The error message seems unrelated to this issue though and it's:

Traceback (most recent call last): File "<string>", line 1, in <module> File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/dist-packages/caffe2/python/core.py", line 14, in <module> from caffe2.proto import caffe2_pb2 File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/dist-packages/caffe2/proto/caffe2_pb2.py", line 168, in <module> options=None, file=DESCRIPTOR), TypeError: __new__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'file'

edit: Since the underlying error is different if you'd like I can open a separate issue and close this one.

body:
Good news is it builds. Bad news is when I try checking if it works with, 

python3 -c 'from caffe2.python import core'

that fails. The error message seems unrelated to this issue though and it's:

`Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<string>", line 1, in <module>
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/dist-packages/caffe2/python/core.py", line 14, in <module>
    from caffe2.proto import caffe2_pb2
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/dist-packages/caffe2/proto/caffe2_pb2.py", line 168, in <module>
    options=None, file=DESCRIPTOR),
TypeError: __new__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'file'`

edit: Since the underlying error is different if you'd like I can open a separate issue and close this one.
